[{"text": "The things we make", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have one supreme quality --", "start": 17.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they live longer than us.", "start": 20.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We perish, they survive;", "start": 22.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we have one life, they have many lives,", "start": 24.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and in each life they can mean different things.", "start": 27.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Which means that, while we all have one biography,", "start": 30.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they have many.", "start": 33.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I want this morning to talk", "start": 35.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the story, the biography -- or rather the biographies --", "start": 37.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of one particular object,", "start": 40.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "one remarkable thing.", "start": 43.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It doesn't, I agree,", "start": 45.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "look very much.", "start": 47.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's about the size of a rugby ball.", "start": 49.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's made of clay,", "start": 52.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it's been fashioned", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into a cylinder shape,", "start": 56.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "covered with close writing", "start": 59.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then baked dry in the sun.", "start": 61.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And as you can see,", "start": 64.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's been knocked about a bit,", "start": 66.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which is not surprising", "start": 68.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because it was made two and a half thousand years ago", "start": 70.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and was dug up", "start": 73.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in 1879.", "start": 75.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But today,", "start": 77.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this thing is, I believe,", "start": 79.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a major player", "start": 81.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the politics of the Middle East.", "start": 83.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it's an object", "start": 85.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with fascinating stories", "start": 87.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and stories that are by no means over yet.", "start": 89.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "The story begins", "start": 93.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the Iran-Iraq war", "start": 95.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and that series of events", "start": 99.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that culminated", "start": 101.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the invasion of Iraq", "start": 103.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by foreign forces,", "start": 105.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the removal of a despotic ruler", "start": 107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and instant regime change.", "start": 109.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And I want to begin", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with one episode from that sequence of events", "start": 114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that most of you would be very familiar with,", "start": 116.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Belshazzar's feast --", "start": 119.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because we're talking about the Iran-Iraq war", "start": 121.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of 539 BC.", "start": 123.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the parallels", "start": 126.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between the events", "start": 128.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of 539 BC and 2003 and in between", "start": 130.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are startling.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What you're looking at is Rembrandt's painting,", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "now in the National Gallery in London,", "start": 137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "illustrating the text from the prophet Daniel", "start": 139.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the Hebrew scriptures.", "start": 141.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And you all know roughly the story.", "start": 144.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Belshazzar, the son of Nebuchadnezzar,", "start": 146.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Nebuchadnezzar who'd conquered Israel, sacked Jerusalem", "start": 149.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and captured the people", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and taken the Jews back to Babylon.", "start": 154.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Not only the Jews, he'd taken the temple vessels.", "start": 156.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He'd ransacked, desecrated the temple.", "start": 159.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the great gold vessels of the temple in Jerusalem", "start": 162.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "had been taken to Babylon.", "start": 165.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Belshazzar, his son,", "start": 168.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "decides to have a feast.", "start": 170.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And in order to make it even more exciting,", "start": 172.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he added a bit of sacrilege to the rest of the fun,", "start": 174.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and he brings out the temple vessels.", "start": 177.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He's already at war with the Iranians,", "start": 180.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with the king of Persia.", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And that night, Daniel tells us,", "start": 185.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "at the height of the festivities", "start": 188.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a hand appeared and wrote on the wall,", "start": 190.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"You are weighed in the balance and found wanting,", "start": 193.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and your kingdom is handed over", "start": 196.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the Medes and the Persians.\"", "start": 198.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And that very night", "start": 200.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Cyrus, king of the Persians, entered Babylon", "start": 202.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and the whole regime of Belshazzar fell.", "start": 206.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "It is, of course, a great moment", "start": 211.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the history", "start": 213.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the Jewish people.", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a great story. It's story we all know.", "start": 217.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"The writing on the wall\"", "start": 219.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is part of our everyday language.", "start": 221.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What happened next", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was remarkable,", "start": 226.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it's where our cylinder", "start": 228.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "enters the story.", "start": 230.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Cyrus, king of the Persians,", "start": 232.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has entered Babylon without a fight --", "start": 234.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the great empire of Babylon,", "start": 236.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which ran from central southern Iraq", "start": 238.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the Mediterranean,", "start": 240.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "falls to Cyrus.", "start": 242.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And Cyrus makes a declaration.", "start": 244.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And that is what this cylinder is,", "start": 248.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the declaration made by the ruler guided by God", "start": 251.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who had toppled the Iraqi despot", "start": 254.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and was going to bring freedom to the people.", "start": 258.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In ringing Babylonian --", "start": 260.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it was written in Babylonian --", "start": 262.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he says, \"I am Cyrus, king of all the universe,", "start": 264.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the great king, the powerful king,", "start": 267.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "king of Babylon, king of the four quarters of the world.\"", "start": 269.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "They're not shy of hyperbole as you can see.", "start": 273.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is probably", "start": 276.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the first real press release", "start": 278.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by a victorious army", "start": 280.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that we've got.", "start": 282.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it's written, as we'll see in due course,", "start": 284.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by very skilled P.R. consultants.", "start": 286.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So the hyperbole is not actually surprising.", "start": 289.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And what is the great king, the powerful king,", "start": 292.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the king of the four quarters of the world going to do?", "start": 294.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He goes on to say that, having conquered Babylon,", "start": 297.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "he will at once let all the peoples", "start": 300.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the Babylonians -- Nebuchadnezzar and Belshazzar --", "start": 303.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have captured and enslaved", "start": 305.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "go free.", "start": 307.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He'll let them return to their countries.", "start": 309.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And more important,", "start": 311.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he will let them all recover", "start": 313.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the gods, the statues,", "start": 315.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the temple vessels", "start": 317.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that had been confiscated.", "start": 319.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "All the peoples that the Babylonians had repressed and removed", "start": 321.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "will go home,", "start": 324.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and they'll take with them their gods.", "start": 326.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they'll be able to restore their altars", "start": 329.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to worship their gods", "start": 332.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in their own way, in their own place.", "start": 334.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is the decree,", "start": 337.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this object is the evidence", "start": 339.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for the fact that the Jews,", "start": 342.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "after the exile in Babylon,", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the years they'd spent sitting by the waters of Babylon,", "start": 346.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "weeping when they remembered Jerusalem,", "start": 349.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "those Jews were allowed to go home.", "start": 352.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They were allowed to return to Jerusalem", "start": 355.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to rebuild the temple.", "start": 357.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a central document", "start": 359.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Jewish history.", "start": 361.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the Book of Chronicles, the Book of Ezra in the Hebrew scriptures", "start": 363.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "reported in ringing terms.", "start": 367.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is the Jewish version", "start": 369.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the same story.", "start": 371.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Thus said Cyrus, king of Persia,", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "'All the kingdoms of the earth have the Lord God of heaven given thee,", "start": 375.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and he has charged me", "start": 378.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to build him a house in Jerusalem.", "start": 380.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Who is there among you of his people?", "start": 382.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Lord God be with him,", "start": 384.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and let him go up.'\"", "start": 386.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Go up\" -- aaleh.", "start": 389.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The central element, still,", "start": 391.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the notion of return,", "start": 394.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a central part", "start": 396.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the life of Judaism.", "start": 398.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "As you all know, that return from exile,", "start": 400.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the second temple,", "start": 402.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "reshaped Judaism.", "start": 404.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And that change,", "start": 406.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that great historic moment,", "start": 408.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was made possible by Cyrus, the king of Persia,", "start": 410.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "reported for us in Hebrew in scripture", "start": 414.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and in Babylonian in clay.", "start": 417.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Two great texts,", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what about the politics?", "start": 422.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What was going on", "start": 424.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was the fundamental shift in Middle Eastern history.", "start": 426.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The empire of Iran, the Medes and the Persians,", "start": 429.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "united under Cyrus,", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "became the first great world empire.", "start": 434.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Cyrus begins in the 530s BC.", "start": 438.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And by the time of his son Darius,", "start": 441.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "the whole of the eastern Mediterranean", "start": 445.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is under Persian control.", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This empire is, in fact,", "start": 450.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Middle East as we now know it,", "start": 452.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it's what shapes the Middle East as we now know it.", "start": 454.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It was the largest empire the world had known until then.", "start": 457.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Much more important,", "start": 459.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it was the first", "start": 461.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "multicultural, multifaith state", "start": 463.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on a huge scale.", "start": 465.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it had to be run in a quite new way.", "start": 467.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It had to be run in different languages.", "start": 469.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The fact that this decree is in Babylonian says one thing.", "start": 471.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it had to recognize their different habits,", "start": 474.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "different peoples, different religions, different faiths.", "start": 476.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "All of those are respected by Cyrus.", "start": 479.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Cyrus sets up a model", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of how you run", "start": 484.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a great multinational, multifaith, multicultural society.", "start": 486.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "And the result of that", "start": 491.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was an empire that included the areas you see on the screen,", "start": 493.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and which survived for 200 years of stability", "start": 496.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "until it was shattered by Alexander.", "start": 499.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It left a dream of the Middle East as a unit,", "start": 502.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and a unit where people of different faiths", "start": 504.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "could live together.", "start": 506.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Greek invasions ended that.", "start": 508.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And of course, Alexander couldn't sustain a government", "start": 510.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and it fragmented.", "start": 513.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But what Cyrus represented", "start": 515.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "remained absolutely central.", "start": 517.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Greek historian Xenophon", "start": 519.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "wrote his book \"Cyropaedia\"", "start": 522.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "promoting Cyrus as the great ruler.", "start": 524.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And throughout European culture afterward,", "start": 526.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Cyrus remained the model.", "start": 529.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a 16th century image", "start": 532.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to show you how widespread", "start": 534.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "his veneration actually was.", "start": 536.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And Xenophon's book on Cyrus", "start": 539.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on how you ran a diverse society", "start": 541.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was one of the great textbooks", "start": 544.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that inspired the Founding Fathers", "start": 546.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the American Revolution.", "start": 548.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Jefferson was a great admirer --", "start": 550.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the ideals of Cyrus", "start": 552.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "obviously speaking to those 18th century ideals", "start": 554.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of how you create religious tolerance", "start": 556.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a new state.", "start": 558.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Meanwhile, back in Babylon,", "start": 563.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "things had not been going well.", "start": 565.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "After Alexander, the other empires,", "start": 567.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Babylon declines, falls into ruins,", "start": 570.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and all the traces of the great Babylonian empire are lost --", "start": 573.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "until 1879", "start": 577.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when the cylinder is discovered", "start": 579.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by a British Museum exhibition digging in Babylon.", "start": 582.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it enters now another story.", "start": 585.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It enters that great debate", "start": 588.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the middle of the 19th century:", "start": 590.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Are the scriptures reliable? Can we trust them?", "start": 592.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We only knew", "start": 595.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the return of the Jews and the decree of Cyrus", "start": 597.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from the Hebrew scriptures.", "start": 599.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "No other evidence.", "start": 601.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Suddenly, this appeared.", "start": 603.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And great excitement", "start": 605.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to a world where those who believed in the scriptures", "start": 607.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "had had their faith in creation shaken", "start": 609.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by evolution, by geology,", "start": 611.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "here was evidence", "start": 613.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the scriptures were historically true.", "start": 615.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a great 19th century moment.", "start": 617.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But -- and this, of course, is where it becomes complicated --", "start": 620.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "the facts were true,", "start": 625.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "hurrah for archeology,", "start": 627.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but the interpretation was rather more complicated.", "start": 630.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Because the cylinder account and the Hebrew Bible account", "start": 633.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "differ in one key respect.", "start": 636.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Babylonian cylinder", "start": 638.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is written by the priests", "start": 640.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the great god of Bablyon, Marduk.", "start": 642.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And, not surprisingly,", "start": 644.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they tell you that all this was done by Marduk.", "start": 646.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Marduk, we hold, called Cyrus by his name.\"", "start": 648.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Marduk takes Cyrus by the hand,", "start": 651.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "calls him to shepherd his people", "start": 654.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and gives him the rule of Babylon.", "start": 656.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Marduk tells Cyrus", "start": 659.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that he will do these great, generous things", "start": 661.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of setting the people free.", "start": 663.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And this is why we should all be grateful to", "start": 665.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and worship Marduk.", "start": 667.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Hebrew writers", "start": 669.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the Old Testament,", "start": 671.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you will not be surprised to learn,", "start": 673.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "take a rather different view of this.", "start": 676.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "For them, of course, it can't possibly by Marduk", "start": 678.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that made all this happen.", "start": 680.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It can only be Jehovah.", "start": 682.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And so in Isaiah,", "start": 684.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we have the wonderful texts", "start": 686.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "giving all the credit of this,", "start": 688.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not to Marduk", "start": 690.26, "duration": 1.0}, {"text": "but to the Lord God of Israel --", "start": 691.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the Lord God of Israel", "start": 694.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who also called Cyrus by name,", "start": 696.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "also takes Cyrus by the hand", "start": 698.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and talks of him shepherding his people.", "start": 701.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a remarkable example", "start": 703.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of two different priestly appropriations of the same event,", "start": 705.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "two different religious takeovers", "start": 709.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of a political fact.", "start": 711.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "God, we know,", "start": 713.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is usually on the side of the big battalions.", "start": 715.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The question is, which god was it?", "start": 717.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the debate unsettles", "start": 720.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "everybody in the 19th century", "start": 722.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to realize that the Hebrew scriptures", "start": 724.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are part of a much wider world of religion.", "start": 726.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it's quite clear", "start": 729.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the cylinder is older than the text of Isaiah,", "start": 731.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and yet, Jehovah is speaking", "start": 734.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in words very similar", "start": 736.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to those used by Marduk.", "start": 738.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And there's a slight sense that Isaiah knows this,", "start": 740.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because he says,", "start": 743.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this is God speaking, of course,", "start": 745.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"I have called thee by thy name", "start": 748.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "though thou hast not known me.\"", "start": 750.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I think it's recognized", "start": 752.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that Cyrus doesn't realize", "start": 754.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that he's acting under orders from Jehovah.", "start": 756.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And equally, he'd have been surprised that he was acting under orders from Marduk.", "start": 759.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Because interestingly, of course,", "start": 762.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Cyrus is a good Iranian", "start": 764.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with a totally different set of gods", "start": 766.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who are not mentioned in any of these texts.", "start": 768.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 770.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That's 1879.", "start": 772.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "40 years on", "start": 774.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we're in 1917,", "start": 776.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the cylinder enters a different world.", "start": 779.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This time, the real politics", "start": 781.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the contemporary world --", "start": 783.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the year of the Balfour Declaration,", "start": 785.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the year when the new imperial power in the Middle East, Britain,", "start": 788.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "decides that it will declare", "start": 791.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Jewish national home,", "start": 793.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it will allow", "start": 795.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Jews to return.", "start": 797.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the response to this", "start": 799.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the Jewish population in Eastern Europe is rhapsodic.", "start": 801.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And across Eastern Europe,", "start": 804.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Jews display pictures of Cyrus", "start": 806.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and of George V", "start": 808.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "side by side --", "start": 810.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the two great rulers", "start": 812.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who have allowed the return to Jerusalem.", "start": 814.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the Cyrus cylinder comes back into public view", "start": 817.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the text of this", "start": 820.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as a demonstration of why what is going to happen", "start": 822.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "after the war is over in 1918", "start": 825.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is part of a divine plan.", "start": 828.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You all know what happened.", "start": 831.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The state of Israel is setup,", "start": 833.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and 50 years later, in the late 60s,", "start": 836.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it's clear that Britain's role as the imperial power is over.", "start": 839.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And another story of the cylinder begins.", "start": 842.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The region, the U.K. and the U.S. decide,", "start": 845.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has to be kept safe from communism,", "start": 847.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the superpower that will be created to do this", "start": 850.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "would be Iran, the Shah.", "start": 853.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And so the Shah invents an Iranian history,", "start": 855.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or a return to Iranian history,", "start": 858.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that puts him in the center of a great tradition", "start": 860.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and produces coins", "start": 863.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "showing himself", "start": 865.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the Cyrus cylinder.", "start": 867.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "When he has his great celebrations in Persepolis,", "start": 869.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "he summons the cylinder", "start": 872.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the cylinder is lent by the British Museum, goes to Tehran,", "start": 874.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and is part of those great celebrations", "start": 877.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the Pahlavi dynasty.", "start": 879.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Cyrus cylinder: guarantor of the Shah.", "start": 882.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "10 years later, another story:", "start": 885.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Iranian Revolution, 1979.", "start": 888.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Islamic revolution, no more Cyrus;", "start": 890.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we're not interested in that history,", "start": 892.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we're interested in Islamic Iran --", "start": 894.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "until Iraq,", "start": 897.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the new superpower that we've all decided should be in the region,", "start": 899.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "attacks.", "start": 902.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Then another Iran-Iraq war.", "start": 904.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it becomes critical for the Iranians", "start": 906.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to remember their great past,", "start": 908.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "their great past", "start": 911.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when they fought Iraq and won.", "start": 913.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It becomes critical to find a symbol", "start": 916.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that will pull together all Iranians --", "start": 918.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Muslims and non-Muslims,", "start": 921.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Christians, Zoroastrians, Jews living in Iran,", "start": 923.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "people who are devout, not devout.", "start": 926.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the obvious emblem is Cyrus.", "start": 928.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So when the British Museum and Tehran National Musuem", "start": 931.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "cooperate and work together, as we've been doing,", "start": 934.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Iranians ask for one thing only", "start": 936.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as a loan.", "start": 938.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's the only object they want.", "start": 940.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They want to borrow the Cyrus cylinder.", "start": 942.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And last year,", "start": 944.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Cyrus cylinder went to Tehran", "start": 946.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "for the second time.", "start": 950.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's shown being presented here, put into its case", "start": 953.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by the director of the National Museum of Tehran,", "start": 956.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "one of the many women in Iran in very senior positions,", "start": 959.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Mrs. Ardakani.", "start": 962.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It was a huge event.", "start": 964.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is the other side of that same picture.", "start": 966.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's seen in Tehran", "start": 969.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by between one and two million people", "start": 972.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the space of a few months.", "start": 974.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is beyond any blockbuster exhibition", "start": 976.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the West.", "start": 978.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it's the subject of a huge debate", "start": 980.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about what this cylinder means, what Cyrus means,", "start": 983.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but above all, Cyrus as articulated through this cylinder --", "start": 986.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Cyrus as the defender of the homeland,", "start": 989.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the champion, of course, of Iranian identity", "start": 992.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and of the Iranian peoples,", "start": 994.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "tolerant of all faiths.", "start": 996.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And in the current Iran,", "start": 998.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Zoroastrians and Christians have guaranteed places", "start": 1000.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the Iranian parliament, something to be very, very proud of.", "start": 1003.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "To see this object in Tehran,", "start": 1006.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "thousands of Jews living in Iran", "start": 1009.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "came to Tehran to see it.", "start": 1011.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It became a great emblem,", "start": 1013.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a great subject of debate", "start": 1015.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about what Iran is at home and abroad.", "start": 1017.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Is Iran still to be the defender of the oppressed?", "start": 1020.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Will Iran set free the people", "start": 1023.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the tyrants have enslaved and expropriated?", "start": 1025.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is heady national rhetoric,", "start": 1028.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and it was all put together", "start": 1031.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a great pageant", "start": 1033.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "launching the return.", "start": 1035.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Here you see this out-sized Cyrus cylinder on the stage", "start": 1037.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with great figures from Iranian history", "start": 1040.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "gathering to take their place", "start": 1043.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the heritage of Iran.", "start": 1045.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It was a narrative presented", "start": 1048.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the president himself.", "start": 1050.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And for me,", "start": 1053.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to take this object to Iran,", "start": 1055.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be allowed to take this object to Iran", "start": 1057.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was to be allowed to be part", "start": 1059.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of an extraordinary debate", "start": 1061.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "led at the highest levels", "start": 1063.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about what Iran is,", "start": 1065.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what different Irans there are", "start": 1067.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and how the different histories of Iran", "start": 1070.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "might shape the world today.", "start": 1072.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a debate that's still continuing,", "start": 1075.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and it will continue to rumble,", "start": 1078.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because this object", "start": 1080.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is one of the great declarations", "start": 1082.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of a human aspiration.", "start": 1084.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It stands with the American constitution.", "start": 1086.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "It certainly says far more about real freedoms", "start": 1090.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "than Magna Carta.", "start": 1093.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It is a document that can mean so many things,", "start": 1095.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for Iran and for the region.", "start": 1098.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A replica of this", "start": 1101.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is at the United Nations.", "start": 1103.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In New York this autumn, it will be present", "start": 1105.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "when the great debates", "start": 1108.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the future of the Middle East take place.", "start": 1110.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And I want to finish by asking you", "start": 1113.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what the next story will be", "start": 1115.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in which this object figures.", "start": 1117.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It will appear, certainly,", "start": 1119.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in many more Middle Eastern stories.", "start": 1121.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And what story of the Middle East,", "start": 1123.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what story of the world,", "start": 1125.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "do you want to see", "start": 1127.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "reflecting what is said,", "start": 1129.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what is expressed in this cylinder?", "start": 1131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The right of peoples", "start": 1133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to live together in the same state,", "start": 1135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "worshiping differently, freely --", "start": 1137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Middle East, a world,", "start": 1139.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in which religion is not the subject of division", "start": 1141.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or of debate.", "start": 1143.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the world of the Middle East at the moment,", "start": 1146.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the debates are, as you know, shrill.", "start": 1149.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But I think it's possible", "start": 1152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the most powerful and the wisest voice of all of them", "start": 1154.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "may well be the voice", "start": 1158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of this mute thing,", "start": 1160.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Cyrus cylinder.", "start": 1162.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1164.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1166.26, "duration": 4.0}]